{"type":"text","timestamp":1782641240038,"sessionID":"ses_0f2531880ffeM0ACoXa0AcPlTY","part":{"id":"prt_f0db26583001Zv75MoveZbfm0z","messageID":"msg_f0db25978001gL8S0IwhvbwUUg","sessionID":"ses_0f2531880ffeM0ACoXa0AcPlTY","type":"text","text":"Implemented batch 1 for `phase-02-startup-session-navigation` on the requested groups.\n\n**What Changed**\n- Tightened phase-02 shared session/menu behavior in `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/session_repository.cj`.\n- Updated detail loading in `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/detail/detail_store.cj` to prefer the selected restaurant snapshot from session state.\n- Strengthened repository coverage tests in `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_repository_contract_test.cj`.\n- Updated only the relevant batch authority rows in `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json` and synced `source-coverage-matrix.md`.\n\n**Key Fix**\n- The source `UserDataRepositoryImpl.setRestaurant()` snapshots the selected restaurant’s exact menu with zero quantities.\n- The target had drifted into shortened hard-coded menu subsets.\n- I expanded the target seed menus so `SessionRepository.setRestaurant()` now preserves the full seeded menu per restaurant, and detail state consumes that selected snapshot first.\n\n**Verification**\n- `phase-02` build gate remains PASS from `translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-02-startup-session-navigation/build-report.md`.\n- I ran one bounded manual test reproduction:\n  - `cjpm test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` in `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie`\n- Current test result:\n  - blocked before phase-02 tests execute because the test package does not expose required production imports for `kit.AbilityKit`, `kit.ArkUI`, and `ohos.resource`.\n- I updated the affected matrix rows to reflect this current harness blocker instead of stale “test pass” wording.\n\n**Authority Updates**\nUpdated batch-relevant rows for:\n- `FoodikeApp.kt` application bootstrap replacement\n- `AppModule.kt` singleton lifecycle replacement and shared login service binding\n- `HomeRepositoryImpl.kt` restaurant list evidence\n- `LoginRepositoryImpl.kt` login toggle and login-state observable contract\n- `UserDataRepositoryImpl.kt` selected restaurant identity and exact menu snapshot contract\n\n**Changed files:**\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/session_repository.cj`: expanded seeded menus to preserve exact per-restaurant snapshot semantics\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/detail/detail_store.cj`: prefer selected session menu snapshot before fallback lookup\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_repository_contract_test.cj`: strengthened repository snapshot assertions and added exact-menu test\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json`: refreshed batch row evidence and current harness-blocked test status\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`: synced from authority patch tool\n\n**Commands run:**\n- `cjpm test --target aarch64-linux-ohos`\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py --kind matrix --authority D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.json --patch D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.tmp-phase02-batch1-matrix-patch.json --markdown D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.md --plan-json D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\plan.json --target-project D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n\n**Build result:**\n- PASS: `translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-02-startup-session-navigation/build-report.md`\n- Manual test reproduction: FAIL/HARNESS-BLOCKED at test-package dependency wiring\n\n**Plan changes:**\n- none\n\n**Deferred issues:**\n- `entry/src/test/cangjie` harness is currently blocked for manual `cjpm test` reproduction because the test package lacks visible kit/resource dependencies required by production imports. Validation needed: one focused test-package wiring fix session, if you want phase-02 test execution restored.\n\n**Next recommended action:**\n- Fix `entry/src/test/cangjie/cjpm.toml` test-package dependency wiring so bounded `phase02_*` tests can execute again, then continue with batch 2/3.","time":{"start":1782641223043,"end":1782641240036}}}
